title: application-gateway-configure-listener-specific-ssl-policy
content:
# Configure listener-specific SSL policies on Application Gateway through portal

**NOTE:** This document discusses configuration through the Azure Portal. Please _always_ use infrastructure-as-code (IaC) for production environments and deploy through Azure DevOps pipelines.

This documentation explains how to configure listener-specific SSL policies on Azure Application Gateway using the Azure portal. Listener-specific SSL policies allow you to configure different SSL policies for specific listeners on your Application Gateway. It is important to note that only the Standard_v2 and WAF_v2 SKUs support listener-specific policies.

To get started, ensure that you have an Azure subscription. If not, you can create a free account before proceeding.

## Create a new Application Gateway

To create a new Application Gateway, follow the usual steps in the Azure portal. There are no additional configuration steps needed to enable listener-specific SSL policies. You can refer to the [portal quickstart tutorial](./quick-create-portal.md) for detailed instructions on creating an Application Gateway.

## Set up a listener-specific SSL policy

Before proceeding with the configuration, keep the following points in mind:

- It is recommended to use TLS 1.2 as it will be mandated in the future.
- You don't need to configure client authentication on an SSL profile to associate it with a listener. You can have either client authentication or a listener-specific SSL policy configured, or both.
- Using a [2022 Predefined](./application-gateway-ssl-policy-overview.md#predefined-tls-policy) or Customv2 policy improves SSL security and performance for the entire gateway. However, it is important to note that you cannot have different listeners using both old and new SSL policies simultaneously.

To set up a listener-specific SSL policy, follow these steps:

1. Search for **Application Gateway** in the Azure portal and select **Application gateways**. Choose your existing Application Gateway.

2. From the left-side menu, select **SSL settings**.

3. Click on the plus sign next to **SSL Profiles** at the top to create a new SSL profile.

4. Provide a name for the SSL profile under **SSL Profile Name**. For example, *applicationGatewaySSLProfile*.

5. Go to the **SSL Policy** tab and check the **Enable listener-specific SSL Policy** box.

6. Configure your listener-specific SSL policy based on your requirements. You can choose from predefined SSL policies or customize your own SSL policy. It is recommended to use TLS 1.2. For more information on SSL policies, refer to the [SSL policy overview](./application-gateway-ssl-policy-overview.md).

7. Click **Add** to save the configuration.
